<br>
<hr><br>
<br>
<b>In my time since I started playing EQ, I have played several characters with the sneak and hide ability combination (including a rogue).<br>
The part I have yet to understand is why only the rogue has a success/failure messsage. Seemings that most classes receive sneak or hide at different levels, it would seem a bit more logical to have a success/fail message, starting at the level you can begin advancement (pay Practice Points into the skill).<br>
<br>
In my opinion, this would not be taking anything away from the rogue class nor making an unbalanced game addition.<br>
<br>
The sneak and hide combination is a very fun and useful part of the EverQuest world and I would like to be able to see more character types be able to take advantage of this ability in a more believable (it is a little hard to believe only a rogue knows whether they have hidden or is truly sneaking) format. Thank you for your time.</b><br>
<br>
The success message is an advantage for the Rogue. The message is not given to other classes with those skills specifically so that it can be an advantage to the rogue. And, actually, it is fairly reasonable. When you're trying to hide behind something it isn't all that easy to tell if you are properly hidden. You may very well have a toe sticking out that you don't know about, or the top of your head may be sticking up (bad hair day, perhaps).<br>
<br>
So, yes, that message is an advantage for the Rogue, and we don't plan to allow other classes to get it.<br>
<br>
